{"id":22,"date":"2024-06-03T15:14:12","date_gmt":"2024-06-03T20:14:12","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/?page_id=22"},"modified":"2024-07-22T13:53:28","modified_gmt":"2024-07-22T18:53:28","slug":"faq","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/what-is-hazing\/faq\/","title":{"rendered":"FAQ"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-cover alignfull has-parallax has-background\" style=\"padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-double);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-double)\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: What is hazing?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: Hazing is when a person intentionally, knowingly or recklessly causes, coerces or forces another individual to engage in or endure certain actions for the purpose of pre-initiation activities, pledging, initiating, holding office, admitting or affiliating into or with an organization, or for the purpose of continuing, reinstating or enhancing an individual&rsquo;s membership or status in an organization. For a more full description, visit the <a href=\"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/what-is-hazing\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">What is Hazing page<\/a>.<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: Is hazing illegal?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: Yes. Hazing is considered a crime.<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: Can I get sued for hazing?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: Yes. In addition to criminal penalties and University sanctions, an individual that engages in hazing could be sued and forced to pay significant monetary damages (along with attorney&#039;s fees) as part of a civil suit. These suits have resulted in judgements totaling millions of dollars. <\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: Isn&#039;t hazing ok if no one gets hurt?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: No. Any form of hazing, regardless of the outcome, is a crime in Louisiana and a violation of University policy. It does not become ok, legal or permissible if no harm is intended or occurs. Additionally, verbal and emotional abuse can be just as damaging as physical abuse. <\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: Have people died from hazing?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: Sadly, yes.&nbsp;There are deaths attributable to hazing at other schools every year.&nbsp;In each of those situations, the individuals that engaged in the hazing probably thought what they were doing was harmless and would not result in someone&rsquo;s death.<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: My group has always hazed new members. I was hazed when I joined. It is a tradition, doesn&#039;t that make it ok?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: No. &quot;Tradition&quot; doesn&#039;t justify committing a crime or violating University policy. Traditions are created by groups and groups hold the power to change or eliminate them. It only takes one year to break a hazing tradition. Remember that the founding members of organizations were not hazed.<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: Our pledges and new members don&#039;t mind getting hazed. They voluntarily participate in these activities, so that can&#039;t be hazing, right?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: Wrong. Under Louisiana state law and GSU policy, the fact that a person consented to a hazing activity is not a defense. The peer pressure and desire to belong in a student organization can creative a coercive environment where true consent cannot be given. In short, an individual cannot consent to being hazed.<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: Doesn&#039;t hazing teach respect and make better members?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: No. Respect is earned, not demanded or taught. When respect is earned, there is also trust. Hazing only motivates people out of fear and anxiety.<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: Doesn&#039;t hazing help build a bond among the pledges and new members?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: No. Hazing isolates each member from the established group. It does not promote organizational unity. There are safer and more productive ways to build friendships and community.<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: Do I have a duty to report hazing?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: Yes.&nbsp;All members of the campus community have an obligation to promptly report any good faith concerns about hazing that has occurred or will occur.<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: If I know about hazing, but don&#039;t promptly report it, what will happen to me?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: If you are a student, you may be subject to charges and sanctions under the Code of Student Conduct. Employees may be subject to discipline.&nbsp;<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: How do I report concerns about hazing?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: If the situation is an emergency and you or someone else needs immediate assistance, please contact The University of Louisiana Police Department (UAPD) at 205-348-5454. For non-emergency situations, find <a href=\"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/report-it\/\">information about reporting options<\/a>.  Any report of hazing should include as much detail as possible (e.g., who, where, when, what happened, etc.).<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: Is it possible to submit an anonymous report?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: Yes. Learn more about <a href=\"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/report-it\/\">reporting options<\/a>. Reporting anonymously, however, does not absolve an individual of other responsibilities related to responding to good faith concerns about hazing, which are noted in the <a href=\"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/what-is-hazing\/ua-hazing-policy\/\">Hazing Policy<\/a>.\u00a0Additionally, anonymous reports complicate the University\u2019s ability to take appropriate action to address any allegations of hazing.\u00a0<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: Am I immune from hazing charges if I make a good faith report of hazing?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: Potentially, yes. To be eligible for that consideration, an individual has to respond to the situation appropriately. For more information on what is expected of an individual in that situation, please closely review the Hazing Policy.<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: Can I report hazing that I think is happening to someone else?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: Yes. You are required under University policy to report any good faith concerns related to hazing activity whether the activity has already occurred or will occur soon.<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: Should I be worried about being removed from the group or punished by the group for reporting hazing?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: No. Retaliation by an individual or organization against an individual who made good faith report of hazing activity is a violation of University policy and will result in significant sanctions.<\/p><\/div><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);min-height:50px;aspect-ratio:unset;\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim-70 has-background-dim\"><\/span><div aria-label=\"Grambling State University students on campus\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-331 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/11\/2025\/gsu-life\/gsu-students-walking.png);\"><\/div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-cover-is-layout-5e48a1f9 wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\"><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-normal-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">Q: What sort of sanctions, punishments or disciplines could I face for engaging in hazing or failing to report hazing?<\/h2><p style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-half)\">A: Sanctions vary and are determined on a case-by-case basis and can include probation, suspension, required counseling, loss of privileges, community service, criminal charges, etc.<\/p><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":331,"parent":17,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"page-content-margin-0-bottom.php","meta":{"hero_blocks":"","sidebar_menu":"","sidebar":false,"sidebar_type":"select","hero":false,"title_alignment":"left","title_width":"standard","footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-22","page","type-page","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/22","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=22"}],"version-history":[{"count":32,"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/22\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":519,"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/22\/revisions\/519"}],"up":[{"embeddable":t